benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.view

Class ObjasnenostView

  • java.lang.Object
    • View
      • benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.view.ObjasnenostView

  • public class ObjasnenostView
extends View
    A class visualizing the numbers of solved and unsolved pie chart.

    A donut chart is used. There are two pie slices. The first pie slice visualizes the crimes solved, the other visualizes the unsolved crimes. The sizes of the two slices are proportionate. In the pie hole, the crime solved ratio value is displayed.

    Author:
    Tom

      • init

      • onDraw

        protected void onDraw(Canvas canvas)
        Draws the pie chart.

        Both the "solved" and "unsolved" pie slices are drawn, the pie hole is drawn atop of them, and finally the crime solved ratio value is drawn atop of everything.

      • onMeasure

        protected void onMeasure(int widthMeasureSpec,
             int heightMeasureSpec)
        Measures the dimensions of this view.

        The smaller of the dimension values is used for both the width and height.

      • onSizeChanged

        protected void onSizeChanged(int w,
                 int h,
                 int oldw,
                 int oldh)
        Calculates the pie chart geometry.

        The bounding rectangle, the pie chart center and the pie chart circle boundaries are calculated.

      • setObjasneno

        public void setObjasneno(float objasneno)
        Sets the crime solved ratio value.

        This invalidates this view, which is possibly followed by the view redrawal.

        Parameters:
        objasneno - the crime solved ratio value to be set
